"./CLAUDE.md:1:<!-- gitnexus:start -->\n./CLAUDE.md:2:# GitNexus — Code Intelligence\n./CLAUDE.md:4:This project is indexed by GitNexus as **Online_Judge** (7128 symbols, 14745 relationships, 300 execution flows). Use the GitNexus MCP tools to understand code, assess impact, and navigate safely.\n./CLAUDE.md:6:> If any GitNexus tool warns the index is stale, run `npx gitnexus analyze` in terminal first.\n./CLAUDE.md:10:- **MUST run impact analysis before editing any symbol.** Before modifying a function, class, or method, run `gitnexus_impact({target: \"symbolName\", direction: \"upstream\"})` and report the blast radius (direct callers, affected processes, risk level) to the user.\n./CLAUDE.md:11:- **MUST run `gitnexus_detect_changes()` before committing** to verify your changes only affect expected symbols and execution flows.\n./CLAUDE.md:13:- When exploring unfamiliar code, use `gitnexus_query({query: \"concept\"})` to find execution flows instead of grepping. It returns process-grouped results ranked by relevance.\n./CLAUDE.md:14:- When you need full context on a specific symbol — callers, callees, which execution flows it participates in — use `gitnexus_context({name: \"symbolName\"})`.\n./CLAUDE.md:18:1. `gitnexus_query({query: \"<error or symptom>\"})` — find execution flows related to the issue\n./CLAUDE.md:19:2. `gitnexus_context({name: \"<suspect function>\"})` — see all callers, callees, and process participation\n./CLAUDE.md:20:3. `READ gitnexus://repo/Online_Judge/process/{processName}` — trace the full execution flow step by step\n./CLAUDE.md:21:4. For regressions: `gitnexus_detect_changes({scope: \"compare\", base_ref: \"main\"})` — see what your branch changed\n./CLAUDE.md:25:- **Renaming**: MUST use `gitnexus_rename({symbol_name: \"old\", new_name: \"new\", dry_run: true})` first. Review the preview — graph edits are safe, text_search edits need manual review. Then run with `dry_run: false`.\n./CLAUDE.md:26:- **Extracting/Splitting**: MUST run `gitnexus_context({name: \"target\"})` to see all incoming/outgoing refs, then `gitnexus_impact({target: \"target\", direction: \"upstream\"})` to find all external callers before moving code.\n./CLAUDE.md:27:- After any refactor: run `gitnexus_detect_changes({scope: \"all\"})` to verify only expected files changed.\n./CLAUDE.md:31:- NEVER edit a function, class, or method without first running `gitnexus_impact` on it.\n./CLAUDE.md:33:- NEVER rename symbols with find-and-replace — use `gitnexus_rename` which understands the call graph.\n./CLAUDE.md:34:- NEVER commit changes without running `gitnexus_detect_changes()` to check affected scope.\n./CLAUDE.md:40:| `query` | Find code by concept | `gitnexus_query({query: \"auth validation\"})` |\n./CLAUDE.md:41:| `context` | 360-degree view of one symbol | `gitnexus_context({name: \"validateUser\"})` |\n./CLAUDE.md:42:| `impact` | Blast radius before editing | `gitnexus_impact({target: \"X\", direction: \"upstream\"})` |\n./CLAUDE.md:43:| `detect_changes` | Pre-commit scope check | `gitnexus_detect_changes({scope: \"staged\"})` |\n./CLAUDE.md:44:| `rename` | Safe multi-file rename | `gitnexus_rename({symbol_name: \"old\", new_name: \"new\", dry_run: true})` |\n./CLAUDE.md:45:| `cypher` | Custom graph queries | `gitnexus_cypher({query: \"MATCH ...\"})` |\n./CLAUDE.md:59:| `gitnexus://repo/Online_Judge/context` | Codebase overview, check index freshness |\n./CLAUDE.md:60:| `gitnexus://repo/Online_Judge/clusters` | All functional areas |\n./CLAUDE.md:61:| `gitnexus://repo/Online_Judge/processes` | All execution flows |\n./CLAUDE.md:62:| `gitnexus://repo/Online_Judge/process/{name}` | Step-by-step execution trace |\n./CLAUDE.md:67:1. `gitnexus_impact` was run for all modified symbols\n./CLAUDE.md:69:3. `gitnexus_detect_changes()` confirms changes match expected scope\n./CLAUDE.md:74:After committing code changes, the GitNexus index becomes stale. Re-run analyze to update it:\n./CLAUDE.md:77:npx gitnexus analyze\n./CLAUDE.md:83:npx gitnexus analyze --embeddings\n./CLAUDE.md:86:To check whether embeddings exist, inspect `.gitnexus/meta.json` — the `stats.embeddings` field shows the count (0 means no embeddings). **Running analyze without `--embeddings` will delete any previously generated embeddings.**\n./CLAUDE.md:94:| Understand architecture / \"How does X work?\" | `.claude/skills/gitnexus/gitnexus-exploring/SKILL.md` |\n./CLAUDE.md:95:| Blast radius / \"What breaks if I change X?\" | `.claude/skills/gitnexus/gitnexus-impact-analysis/SKILL.md` |\n./CLAUDE.md:96:| Trace bugs / \"Why is X failing?\" | `.claude/skills/gitnexus/gitnexus-debugging/SKILL.md` |\n./CLAUDE.md:97:| Rename / extract / split / refactor | `.claude/skills/gitnexus/gitnexus-refactoring/SKILL.md` |\n./CLAUDE.md:98:| Tools, resources, schema reference | `.claude/skills/gitnexus/gitnexus-guide/SKILL.md` |\n./CLAUDE.md:99:| Index, status, clean, wiki CLI commands | `.claude/skills/gitnexus/gitnexus-cli/SKILL.md` |\n./CLAUDE.md:101:<!-- gitnexus:end -->\n./AGENTS.md:1:<!-- gitnexus:start -->\n./AGENTS.md:2:# GitNexus — Code Intelligence\n./AGENTS.md:4:This project is indexed by GitNexus as **Online_Judge** (7128 symbols, 14745 relationships, 300 execution flows). Use the GitNexus MCP tools to understand code, assess impact, and navigate safely.\n./AGENTS.md:6:> If any GitNexus tool warns the index is stale, run `npx gitnexus analyze` in terminal first.\n./AGENTS.md:10:- **MUST run impact analysis before editing any symbol.** Before modifying a function, class, or method, run `gitnexus_impact({target: \"symbolName\", direction: \"upstream\"})` and report the blast radius (direct callers, affected processes, risk level) to the user.\n./AGENTS.md:11:- **MUST run `gitnexus_detect_changes()` before committing** to verify your changes only affect expected symbols and execution flows.\n./AGENTS.md:13:- When exploring unfamiliar code, use `gitnexus_query({query: \"concept\"})` to find execution flows instead of grepping. It returns p